ashire, England"},"en":{"1407–1447":"1407–1447","1410–1446":"1410–1446","1435–1515":"1435–1515","1376–1422":"1376–1422","1381–Female":"1381–Deceased","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","1422":"1422","1410":"1410","about 1435":"about 1435","1376":"1376","1381":"1381","1407":"1407","1515":"1515","Esthwaite Hall, Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sandes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Sands  .","Galician: habitational name from any of various places so named in Galicia (Spain). Compare   Sandez  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Sands","meanings":["English and Scottish: topographic name from Middle English <i>sandes</i> ‘sands’, for someone who lived at or near a sandy place, or a habitational name from a place so named, such as Sands in Carlisle (Cumberland) or Sands Cottages in West Hoathly (Sussex). See   Sand  , of which <i>Sands</i> may sometimes be a plural form or a variant, with excrescent <i>-s</i>. Compare also   Sandes   and   Sandys  .","History: Comfort Sands, a revolutionary patriot born in 1748 at what is now Sands’ Point, Long Island, NY, was descended from James Sand(y)s (1622–95), who emigrated from Reading, Berkshire, England, to Plymouth, MA, and followed Anne Hutchinson to Westchester County, NY, and subsequently RI. In 1661 he settled on Block Island, RI."]},{"name":"Sandez","meanings":["Galician: variant of   Sandes  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Sandes was born in 1407, in Hawkshead, Lancashire, England, his father, John del Sandes, was 31 and his mother, unknown, was 26. He had at least 1 son with de Betham. He died in 1447, in Hawkshead, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1407–1447":"1407–1447","1410–1446":"1410–1446","1435–1515":"1435–1515","1376–1422":"1376–1422","1381–Female":"1381–Surnud","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","1422":"1422","1410":"1410","about 1435":"umbes 1435","1376":"1376","1381":"1381","1407":"1407","1515":"1515","Esthwaite Hall, Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1407–1447":"1407–1447","1410–1446":"1410–1446","1435–1515":"1435–1515","1376–1422":"1376–1422","1381–Female":"1381–Kuollut","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","1422":"1422","1410":"1410","about 1435":"noin 1435","1376":"1376","1381":"1381","1407":"1407","1515":"1515","Esthwaite Hall, Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1407–1447":"1407–1447","1410–1446":"1410–1446","1435–1515":"1435–1515","1376–1422":"1376–1422","1381–Female":"1381–Décédée","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1435":"1435","1422":"1422","1410":"1410","about 1435":"environ 1435","1376":"1376","1381":"1381","1407":"1407","1515":"1515","Esthwaite Hall, Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hawkshead, Lancashire, England":"Hawkshead, Lancashire